# Supabase Configuration
# Get these values from your Supabase project settings (https://app.supabase.com)
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project.supabase.co
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-anon-key-here

# Auth Redirect URL
# Where users should be redirected after clicking magic link in email
# For local development:
VITE_AUTH_REDIRECT_URL=http://localhost:3000
# For production, set to your production URL:
# VITE_AUTH_REDIRECT_URL=https://cms.yourdomain.com

# IMPORTANT: You must add this URL to Supabase's allowed redirect URLs:
# 1. Go to Supabase Dashboard > Authentication > URL Configuration
# 2. Add your URL (e.g., http://localhost:3000) to "Redirect URLs"
# 3. If you have multiple environments, add all of them (comma-separated)

# Note: Magic link authentication requires SMTP to be configured in your Supabase project
# Go to: Supabase Dashboard > Project Settings > Auth > SMTP Settings

# Backend API Configuration
# The backend API URL is configured in vite.config.ts as a proxy
# By default, it proxies /api requests to http://localhost:3001
# If you need to change this, edit the proxy configuration in vite.config.ts

# WebSocket Configuration
# The WebSocket connection is configured in src/lib/socket.ts
# By default, it connects to http://localhost:3001
# If you need to change this, edit the socket configuration in src/lib/socket.ts

# Temporal UI Configuration
# The Temporal UI URL is hardcoded in src/components/PatientCase/WorkflowCard.tsx
# By default, it links to http://localhost:8233
# If you need to change this, edit the URL in WorkflowCard.tsx
